00:00:06,405 --> 00:00:22,554
I Australien har de utövande uppdraget och fortsatta experiment i skogsbrevning av män som John MacArthur spelat en viktig del i att ständigt stödja Australiens största pastoralindustri.

3
00:00:22,574 --> 00:00:28,318
Skogsbrevaren, som ständigt strävar för att förbättra hans flok, betalar ofta fabulösa pengar för studdramar.

4
00:00:29,774 --> 00:00:34,697
During that period of useful life, these monarchs of the flock are treated with luxurious attention.

5
00:00:36,518 --> 00:00:45,661
Systematic crossbreeding produced the Australian merino, a very hardy sheep, carrying an exceptionally heavy fleece of wool of superb quality.

6
00:00:47,241 --> 00:00:52,743
More than one quarter of the total wool of the world is produced in Australia under natural conditions.

7
00:00:56,685 --> 00:00:59,225
At mustering time, all hands and the cook are busy.

8
00:00:59,929 --> 00:01:06,593
The flockmaster's daughter adds to the picturesqueness of the scene as she operates the drafting gate separating the ewes from the lambs.

9
00:01:08,995 --> 00:01:10,956
Healthy sheep produce the finest wool.

10
00:01:10,977 --> 00:01:15,301
Therefore precautionary measures are taken to ensure immunity from natural ills.

11
